V biu 

target_count <- function(data) {
  outcome_counts <- table(data$group)
  outcomes <- names(outcome_counts)
  counts <- as.numeric(outcome_counts)
  ggplot(aes(x = counts, y = outcomes), data = data.frame(counts, outcomes)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = c("lightskyblue", "gold"), color = "black") +
    labs(title = "Count of Outcome Variable", x = "Number of Individuals", y = "Outcome") +
    coord_flip() +
    theme_bw() +
    theme(text = element_text(size = 15))
}
target_count(new_diabetes)

nA <- sum(new_diabetes$group == 'Diabetes')
nB <- sum(new_diabetes$group == 'No diabetes')

Permutation function: tnh ton s khc bit trung bnh qua hon v

perm_fun <- function(x, nA, nB, R) {
  n <- nA + nB
  mean_diff <- numeric(R)
  for (i in 1:R){
    idx_a <- sample(x = 1:n, size = nA)
    idx_b <- setdiff(x = 1:n, y = idx_a)
    mean_diff[i] <- mean(x[idx_a]) - mean(x[idx_b])
  }
  return(mean_diff)
}

To phn phi khc bit trung bnh qua 100 php th

set.seed(21)
R <- 100
diff_mean_perm <- perm_fun(new_diabetes$bmi, nA, nB, R)

Tnh ton cc gi tr trung bnh BMI ca 2 nhm

mean_a <- mean(new_diabetes$bmi[new_diabetes$group == 'Diabetes'])
mean_b <- mean(new_diabetes$bmi[new_diabetes$group == 'No diabetes'])

Tnh gi tr p-value v in ra kt qu

p_value <- mean(abs(diff_mean_perm) >= abs(mean_a - mean_b))

Logistic Regression Model with Cross-validation

# Kt hp X_train_scaled v y_train  to d liu hun luyn hon chnh
train_data_final <- data.frame(X_train_scaled, group = y_train)

# Hun luyn m hnh logistic regression s dng glmnet
set.seed(123) # m bo tnh ti lp
model_logistic <- train(
  group ~ ., 
  data = train_data_final,
  method = "glmnet",
  family = "binomial",
  metric = "Accuracy",
  trControl = trainControl(
    method = "cv", 
    number = 10, 
    verboseIter = FALSE
  )
)
# D on trn tp kim tra
y_pred_probs <- predict(model_logistic, newdata = X_test_scaled, type = "prob")

# p dng ngng 0.5  phn loi
y_pred_logistic <- ifelse(y_pred_probs[, 2] > 0.5, "1", "0")

# m bo levels ca y_test v y_pred_logistic ging nhau
levels(y_pred_logistic) <- levels(y_test)

# nh gi m hnh (accuracy)
accuracy_logistic <- mean(y_test == y_pred_logistic)

# Ma trn nhm ln (confusion matrix)
class_report_logistic <- caret::confusionMatrix(y_pred_logistic, y_test)

Nhn xt m hnh:

  1. nh gi tng quan v hiu sut:
  • Accuracy ( chnh xc):
+   Gi tr l 70.42%, cho thy rng m hnh c th d on ng hn 70% trng hp.

+   Tuy nhin, gi tr No Information Rate (NIR) l 84.24% (t l mu thuc nhm khng bnh tiu ng).

-> iu ny ng rng nu ch d on tt c l khng b bnh, chnh xc s cao hn, ngha l m hnh cha khai thc c y thng tin.

  • Balanced Accuracy ( chnh xc cn bng):
+   Gi tr 71.52% cho thy m hnh  phn no x l c mt cn bng trong d liu. Tuy nhin, kt qu vn khng cao, c th do d liu c s chnh lch ln gia s ngi bnh v khng bnh.
  1. Hiu sut theo tng lp (Diabetes/No diabetes):
  • Sensitivity ( nhy, T l Dng tnh tht):
+   Gi tr l 73.12%, ngha l trong s ngi thc s mc bnh, m hnh d on ng c hn 73%. y l mt mc  kh n trong vic pht hin bnh, nhng cn ci thin  gim thiu b st cc trng hp bnh.

_ Specificity ( c hiu, T l m tnh tht):

+   Gi tr l 69.92%, cho bit hn 69% ngi khng mc bnh c d on ng. iu ny thp hn mt cht so vi  nhy, dn n m hnh c khuynh hng pht hin ngi bnh tt hn l xc nh ngi khng bnh.
  • Positive Predictive Value (Precision):
+   Gi tr l 31.26%, ngha l ch khong 31% cc d on "b tiu ng" l chnh xc. y l mt im yu ca m hnh, nguyn nhn c th l: D liu mt cn bng: Nhm "khng bnh" chim u th ln.

-> chnh xc ca d on dng tnh thp khin vic p dng thc t c nguy c tng s lng chn on sai.

  • Negative Predictive Value (NPV):
+   Gi tr l 93.29%, cho thy rng trong s cc trng hp d on "khng mc bnh," 93.29% l chnh xc. iu ny khng nh kh nng loi tr ngi khng mc bnh l kh tt.
  1. Kt lun:
  • Mc d Logistic Regression l mt khi u tt vi chnh xc tng qut 70.42%, nhng m hnh hin gp kh khn trong vic pht hin ng ngi b bnh (Precision thp). y l vn quan trng v trong y hc, b st ngi b bnh tiu ng c th gy ra hu qu nghim trng.

-> Cn ci thin bng cch cn bng d liu, th nghim m hnh phc tp hn v ti u ha cc tham s m hnh t c hiu sut cao hn trong vic phn loi.

-> V vy nhm em xut mt m hnh phn loi khc l Random Forrest.

  1. Sensitivity v Specificity:

_ Sensitivity (T l pht hin bnh): 50.03%. M hnh ch pht hin c ~50% trng hp b tiu ng. y l mc kh thp, nht l trong cc bi ton y t ni vic pht hin bnh chnh xc l rt quan trng.

  • Specificity (T l pht hin khng mc bnh): 83.99%. M hnh rt tt trong vic d on nhng ngi khng b tiu ng, vi t l ng ~84%.
  1. Positive Predictive Value (PPV) v Negative Predictive Value (NPV):

  • NPV (Precision cho khng tiu ng): 89.99%. Trong cc trng hp d on khng b tiu ng, gn 90% l ng.

  1. Kt lun:

  • M hnh c chnh xc tng th tng i tt (78.64%).

  • T l pht hin nhm Khng b tiu ng (Specificity) rt cao (~84%).

-> M hnh Random Forest ph hp d on nhm Khng b tiu ng nh Specificity cao, nhng kh nng pht hin ngi bnh (Sensitivity) cha tt ng dng trong thc t y t.
